<SLUG> BC-NY-HORSES-FIRE-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
9 HORSES REPORTED DEAD IN STABLE FIRE  

</HEADLINE>
   c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ At least nine horses died Friday night when a fire
broke out in a Brooklyn stable, fire officials said.
</P>
<P>
   Vito Berretta, a Fire Department spokesman, said the roof of
Bergen Beach Stables, a wood-frame building in the Bergen Beach
neighborhood, collapsed during the fire. He said nine horses were
confirmed dead, and at least four others escaped safely. Usually
there are about 25 horses in the stable, but there might have been
fewer on a weekend, he said.
</P>
<P>
   The fire was reported shortly before midnight and extinguished
about 1 a.m., Berretta said.
</P>
<P>
   The cause of the fire was unknown.
</P>
</TEXT>
