<P>
   &UR; EUROPE &LR;  &QC;  &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; BEST OF FOES: PUTIN, CLINTON ARE DIPLOMACY'S ARTFUL DODGERS &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; PUTIN-CLINTON-DUEL-ECONOMIST &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (UNDATED) _ With no pretense to personal warmth, U.S. President
Bill Clinton and Russian President Vladimir Putin artfully finessed
their differences over strategic issues, particularly anti-missile
defenses, in a way that enabled each to claim success from their
first summit meeting while still looking good at home. But the gap
between American and Russian views remain as wide as the Volga. &QL;
</P>
