<P>
   SCIENCE/MEDICINE
</P>
<P>
   GECKOS _ WASHINGTON _ High-speed photography has revealed the
secret that allows gecko lizards to scurry up sheer walls or along
the underside of ceilings. Hundreds of millions of microscopic
hairs on the lizards' feet enable them to invoke a form of atomic
energy known as the ``van der Waals force.'' The force causes atoms
to cling to each other and enables geckos to cling to just about
anything. Berkeley University researchers describe their research
in the journal Nature on Thursday. (Nesmith, Cox News Service).
With PHOTOS from Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: MOVED FOR USE THURSDAY.
</P>
<P>
   WAN Location Atlanta, category Science/Medicine, subcategory
General Science
