<P>
   Bureau chie point. Foxworthy is more in his element telling
jokes and cutting up in front of a bunch of country music
enthusiasts. His blue-collar humor about NASCAR drivers and growing
old doesn't appeal to everyone. However, as Hughes points out,
enough people can relate to it because it's ``Americana and it's
not blue.''
</P>
<P>
   The TNN Music Awards is country music's only fan-voted awards
show. Awards will be handed out in 12 categories based on fan votes
cast in Country Weekly, by 900 numbers and on the Internet. Faith
Hill (''Breathe'') leads with eight nominations, followed by George
Strait (''Always Never The Same'') with six and Tim McGraw (''A
Place in the Sun'') with five. Hill, McGraw, Strait, Alan Jackson
and Shania Twain were nominated for Entertainer of the Year.
Jackson was also nominated for Male Artist of the Year, Album of
the Year and The Impact Award.
</P>
<P>
   Now, what would a music awards show be without performances?
Clint Black, Lisa Hartman Black, The Wilkinsons and Faith Hill are
among those scheduled to perform. Hopefully the producers will put
the sultry Hill next to wind-blowing machine like VH1 did for Divas
2000.
</P>
<P>
   Unlike the formal Country Music Awards, the TNN Music Awards is
more of a free-wheeling affair. It's the Golden Globes of country
music awards, while the CMA is more like the stuffy Oscar ceremony.
``This is all about the fans,'' Hughes explains. ``There's an
informality about the show, an excitement about the show and a
spontaneity. With no bad feeling towards the CMA, but our show is
different. And it's supposed to be different.''
</P>
