u s BC-BKN-PACERS-NYT &LR;      06-10 0636
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-PACERS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LAKERS HAVE WON BEFORE WITHOUT STAR GUARD 
</HEADLINE>
   By TOM SPOUSTA   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Kobe Bryant hobbled into the postgame interview
area on crutches, the pain from his sprained left ankle relieved
somewhat by his team's victory. As Bryant collapsed on the floor
early in Game 2 on Friday night, the Los Angeles Lakers' hopes for
holding home-court advantage seemed to fall with him.
</P>
<P>
   Instead, the Lakers turned back several rallies by the Indiana
Pacers to win, 111-104, and take a 2-0 lead in games in the
four-of-seven-game National Basketball Association finals.
</P>
<P>
   The outcome required Ron Harper and Glen Rice to score 21 points
each, but the Lakers pointed to the fact that they had survived
before without Bryant.
</P>
<P>
   Much as they did when Bryant missed the first 15 games of this
season with a broken hand, the Lakers focused harder and continued
to run their triangle offense. Shaquille O'Neal responded to
Bryant's absence with 40 points and 24 rebounds.
</P>
<P>
   Bryant is not expected to play Sunday night in Game 3 at Conseco
Fieldhouse in Indianapolis and could be sidelined for Game 4 on
Wednesday. X-rays taken after he rolled his ankle with 3 minutes 26
seconds remaining in the first quarter were negative, and the
injury was diagnosed as a moderate sprain.
</P>
<P>
   Bryant injured the same ankle in Game 5 of the Western
Conference finals and missed two practices, but returned in time
for Game 6.
</P>
<P>
   Bryant had been undergoing therapy on the ankle, using
range-of-motion exercises to increase flexibility and strength.
</P>
<P>
   The crowd at the Staples Center on Friday night went silent when
Bryant landed awkwardly on the side of Jalen Rose's foot as Rose
came out to contest Bryant on the right wing. Bryant made his jump
shot to give the Lakers a 22-20 lead, but his left foot landed on
Rose's left foot, and Bryant's ankle twisted. Rose did not flinch,
but Bryant rolled on the court in pain and was taken to the locker
room.
</P>
<P>
   ``This was no mystery to us,'' Coach Phil Jackson of the Lakers
said. ``We just said: `Go out there and play the way you know how
to play. Take the shots that become available, don't hesitate,
don't look for someone else. You have to pick it up.' And they
did.''
</P>
<P>
   The reserve guard Derek Fisher said: ``It's more a feeling you
have as a player when one of your guys is out. Not a lot has to be
said because everybody understands the situation. You just focus on
doing your job, and when everybody does that, we're O.K.''
</P>
<P>
   With Bryant's status in doubt _ he is listed as day to day _ the
Lakers will again look toward Rice, Harper and Robert Horry to pick
up the offensive slack.
</P>
<P>
   Rice compensated for Bryant's absence by scoring 13 of his 21
points in the first half. Rice made seven of 15 shots overall,
including five of six 3-pointers.
</P>
<P>
   Harper's 21 points came on eight-of-12 shooting. He also handed
out six assists.
</P>
<P>
   Horry scored only seven points, but made a key 3-point play with
58.8 seconds left to give the Lakers a 102-96 lead after the Pacers
had pulled to within 99-96.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have a lot of guys on this team,'' O'Neal said. ``We have a
lot of weapons on this team.
</P>
<P>
   ``Kobe going out, it just gave Glen and the others a lot more
touches, a lot more opportunities.''
</P>
<P>
   The backup guard Brian Shaw added: ``We were able to win games
earlier in the season without Kobe. That will help our confidence a
lot.''
</P>
<P>
   No matter the prognosis for Bryant's injury, Jackson planned to
evaluate the situation on a daily basis.
</P>
<P>
   ``Obviously, Kobe's the kind of player that will get up off the
floor and play if he could,'' Jackson said. ``We know that. And
when we heard that he was possibly out for the game, I knew it was
going to be serious enough to threaten another game in two days.''
</P>
</TEXT>
