<P>
   GLF-OPEN-STEWART _ When Payne Stewart's plane crashed last
September, four major players stepped to the forefront in the
ensuing 48 hours. Paul Azinger gave a moving speech at the memorial
service in Orlando. Tom Lehman's moment, was a moving speech at a
memorial in Houston where that week's tournament was played. Davis
Love III, who lost his father in a plane crash in the late '80s,
began wearing a What Would Jesus Do bracelet. Lee Janzen, a two
time U.S. Open champ who outdueled Stewart both times he won, was
among the first to arrive at the Stewart home. In a tribute to
Stewart, we show how the tragedy affected the lives of these four
golfers and fathers, in the ensuing 10 months. (Sheeley, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 50. MOVED.
