<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT-FUTURE _ WASHINGTON _ Far from breaking up as a
federal court has ordered, Microsoft is preparing to roll out
``Next Generation Window Services'' that would make the company
more integrated and far-reaching than ever. The plan calls for
tight integration of the computer operating system and a Web
browser that would let people use a number of devices _ including
PCs, handheld computers and Web-enabled telephones _ to access
application programs and data stored on Internet servers. The plan,
often called a blueprint for Microsoft's future, seems incompatible
with the antitrust regulators' vision. (Glass, Cox News Service).
</P>
