   WAN: Location Atlanta, category business, subcategory technology
</P>
<P>
   TECH-CONGRESS _ WASHINGTON _ Many of the most powerful
executives in the U.S. tech industry spent much of last week on
Capitol Hill, telling Congress what they need to extend their
string of innovation and economic success. But because of
old-fashioned political wrangling, three of the industry's top
priorities _ digital signatures, an Internet tax moratorium and
more H-1B visas _ are stuck in Congress with uncertain prospects of
early action. (Geewax, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   EDs: MOVED Friday in (w) Washington and (f) financial
categories.
