<P>
   (NYT1) UNDATED -- June 10, 2000 -- ENGLAND-SOCCER-THUGS -- On
Monday a biennial Europewide soccer competition is being held in
Belgium and the Netherlands. English police will be there to start
the contest, as they have the best reputation for handling
rampaging soccer thugs. Aware that the public shares their desire
to rein in the army of soccer toughs, the police have posted
``England needs you'' advertisements asking people to phone a
number known as the ``hooligan hot line'' with information about
rabble-rousers. (Nancy Siesel/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
