<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-10 23:13 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A0682 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r s BC-BKN-LAKERS-PACERS-LAD     06-10 0809
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKERS-PACERS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SHAQ MIGHT HAVE TO CARRY LAKERS AGAIN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   INDIANAPOLIS _ If a city's faith, a team's hopes and a
franchise's pride can be summed up in a singular image, it is this
one: Kobe Bryant, arriving at practice Saturday afternoon, riding
piggyback on Shaquille O'Neal.
</P>
<P>
   No master's degree in English is needed, no Cliffs Notes
necessary to grasp the obvious symbolism.
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers, eyeing their first championship in 12 years, have a
comfortable 2-0 lead in the NBA Finals. ...
</P>
<P>
   And a very uncomfortable All-Star shooting guard, nursing a
sprained left ankle. ...
</P>
<P>
   But a very sturdy MVP, on whose shoulders everything could rest
when the series resumes this evening with Game 3 at Conseco
Fieldhouse.
</P>
<P>
   So O'Neal carried Bryant _ his status today very much in doubt _
off the team bus. And today, he might need to make room on that
broad back for the rest of the roster and the entire population of
Southern California.
</P>
<P>
   ``I didn't want him to walk on his own,'' O'Neal said. So,
someone surmised, he carried him like he has all year? ``Something
like that.''
</P>
<P>
   Officially, Bryant is a gametime decision, but was still on
crutches and the Lakers are planning for Game 3 as if he will not
be available. That means a heavier burden for O'Neal, averaging
41.5 points in the series.
</P>
<P>
   But it also means another opportunity for the league's best
third option: Glen Rice.
</P>
<P>
   Rice scored 21 points Friday night when Bryant went down in the
first quarter, helping the Lakers secure a 111-104 victory. Once
one of the league's top scorers, Rice has often been an
afterthought in the Shaq &AMP; Kobe Show, averaging 15.9 points in the
regular season, 12.6 in the playoffs.
</P>
<P>
   But when an All-Star falters or is felled, Rice has made it
clear that he remains a deadly shooter. Witness the month of
November when, with Bryant recovering from a broken right hand,
Rice averaged 17.9 points andshot 45.7 percent (compared to 15.4
and 42.3 the rest of the season).
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers can afford a Kobe-less loss today, but they can also
be confident that a 3-0 lead is possible with Rice picking up the
slack.
</P>
<P>
   ``Glen's been great as far as just being patient, and when the
challenge is there and the moment comes, he steps up. He's
responded,'' Bryant said. ``I don't think people truly understand
the sacrifice that Glen Rice had to make. I don't think people
realize what kind of player he was in Charlotte. He put points up
on the board, man. And to come here and be able to give that up is
sacrificing. Plus the demands that we have for him defensively.
Glen's been terrific.''
</P>
<P>
   There is no shortage of incentive for Rice to deliver another
clutch performance.
</P>
<P>
   He is seeking his first championship ring, in his 11th pro
campaign. He is seeking a reward for subverting his ego and his
game the last two seasons following his trade to the Lakers. And
ultimately, as a free agent this summer, he can use any opportunity
to reassure 29 NBA executives that, at 33, he's still an elite
player worthy of one last big contract.
</P>
<P>
   Rice has delicately steered clear of those issues, preferring to
focus on the task at hand, and that task today is clear.
</P>
<P>
   ``I definitely realize I've got to take advantage of (Bryant's
absence),'' he said. ``(Today's) game we're going to be short one
key guy on this ballclub. It's a must that I step my game up.''
</P>
<P>
   If Bryant is out, coach Phil Jackson will mix a few ``specials''
_ plays run specifically for Rice _ into the offense.
</P>
<P>
   ``We called Glen's number a couple of times (Friday) night and
he came through for us,'' Jackson said. ``We ran some things (out
of) timeouts and he was there. But he's going to have to find his
way in the game andhave a nose for it, so to speak. Usually, if a
player gets on a roll, it'll happen for him.''
</P>
<P>
   It did in Game 2, as Rice went 7 for 15 from the field, making 5
of 6 3-pointers. He has quietly contributed all season, despite the
offseason uncertainty and even early season speculation he would be
traded.
</P>
<P>
   ``Glen's handled this situation now about as much as a
professional as anybody could,'' said teammate Derek Fisher. ``And
being the third option on a team where he's definitely capable of
being much more than that. And he just bides his time and waits his
turn. And if Kobe doesn't get a chance to play (today), I think all
eyes will be on him to see how heperforms.''
</P>
<P>
   Said O'Neal, ``I'm sure Glen's going to step up, especially if
Kobe doesn't play, he'll get a whole bunch more shots. ... He's
been a vital part to this offense. Even though he hasn't scored a
lot of points, he's hit a lot of big baskets for us, a lot of big
3s for us. So I'm glad he's here. A big man always wants a shooter
around.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
