INCOME-TAX _ A citizens group has been amassing signatures to place
on the November ballot a proposal to abolish Arizona's state income
tax. The movement has state leaders so alarmed that they have
launched an all-out, largely behind-the-scenes assault on the
supporters behind the plan, hoping to hobble the measure from
making it on the Nov. 7 ballot. Story will move in the ``A''
category.
</P>
