   &QL; 
SHOOTING _ Within a 72-hour period last February, Bricie Tribble
went from a puzzling victim to hero to suspect in a murder
conspiracy. Four months later, Apache Junction police are still
unraveling a case that includes a killing that may or may not have
been self-defense, a dead man with no traceable past, a mysterious
package filled with potentially incriminating evidence, and notes
on a corpse that ended Tribble's brief status as a National Rifle
Association poster child. Story will move in the ``A'' category.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
MONTINI-COLUMN (Phoenix) _ Fourteen years ago this month, I spoke
for the first time to a grieving mother named Dolores Heil. It was
about a week after Heil's daughter had been killed by a stray
bullet while sunning near the pool of a Mesa motel. Heil was hoping
we'd learn a lesson from what happened. We haven't By E.J. MONTINI.
Story will move in the ``A'' and ``K'' categories. &QL; 
