presidential race that culminates with the July 2 election
acknowledges that their country faces an enormous problem with
corruption and among government officials who have sold themselves
to drug traffickers. Story will move in the ``A'' category.  &QL; 
BORDER _ No matter who wins the July 2 Mexican election, volatility
along the Arizona-Mexico border isn't going away, analysts say. In
fact, there is a possibility that it could escalate. Story will
move in the ``A'' category. &QL;
</P>
